description:
Chronos sends Superman and Batman back in time to pivotal points in history in "The Time of Your Life."

  1. Cover by Rich Buckler and Karl Kesel.
  2. "The Time of Your Life" written by Joey Cavalieri, penciled by Jose Delbo, inked by Alfredo Alcala, colored by Nansi Hoolahan and lettered by Duncan Andrew.

Notes:

  • The events in this issue occurred before the Crisis on Infinite Earths mini-series.
  • Batman's villains appear only on the title page.

  • Recaps Chronos' history.
name: The Time of Your Life

description:
Batman helps a female cop search for a mob that she thinks killed her sister; said mob attacks Superman with a ray that contaminates his blood.

name: The Search

description:
Shaka: Close to Godhood!

In their quest to conquer the 12 palaces of the Gold Knights, the Bronze Knights have made unthinkable sacrifices, fought desperate battles, and faced death time and again. Now, with the rebellious Phoenix Knight, Ikki, reluctantly joining their mission, the Bronze Knights are certain victory is finally at hand. Little do they know that their most soul-shattering conflicts are still ahead of them. They're about to face Shaka, who draws his strength from the sacred power of Buddhist belief, and who is so untouchable that even his fellow Gold Knights call him godlike. When Shaka opens his eyes, no mortal can survive his gaze. Ikki doesn't know it, but he's met Shaka once beforeand when he meets him again, he will have no choice but to bow down in terror!
name: Shaka: Close to Godhood!

description: "Hare 'Em, Scare 'Em" Part 2" Last issue found Sonic and Tails falsely blamed for a robot attack and thrown in the clink with that rotten Eggman and his cronies! Now, Sonic's friends are left to the mercy of someone who has no mercy: the ghastly ghost King Boom Boo and his poltergeist pals. With Sonic and Tails incarcerated and Knuckles nowhere to be found, who will save Chris, Cream, and Cheese from this awful apparition? Features Creepily-cool manga art from fan favorite David Hutchison (Antarctic Press' Wizard of Oz)! With a Specter-splatting cover by Spaz!
name: Ghouls Galore!
